      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "discussion",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Users who wish to prolong their iPhoneâ€™s battery life can enable Low Power Mode under Settings > Battery. In Low Power Mode, iOS conserves battery life by enacting certain energy-saving measures, such as reducing CPU and GPU performance, reducing screen brightness, and pausing discretionary and background activities. Your app can query the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "lowPowerModeEnabled"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property at any time to determine whether Low Power Mode is active."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Your app can also register to receive notifications when the power state (Low Power Mode is enabled or disabled) of an iOS device changes. To register for power state notifications, send the message "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsnotificationcenter/1415360-addobserver"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to the default notification center of your app (an instance of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsnotificationcenter"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "). Pass it a selector to call and a notification name of "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nsprocessinfopowerstatedidchangenotification"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ". Once your app is notified of a power state change, it should then query "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "isLowPowerModeEnabled"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " to determine the current power state. If Low Power Mode is active, then your app can take appropriate steps to reduce activity. Otherwise, it can resume normal operations."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "For additional information, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "link",
              "title": "React to Low Power Mode on iPhones",
              "destination": "https://developer.apple.com/library/archive/documentation/Performance/Conceptual/EnergyGuide-iOS/LowPowerMode.html#//apple_ref/doc/uid/TP40015243-CH31"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " in "
            },
            {
